    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="377"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">368.117/138</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 285</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence concerning
                    the impressment of American citizens into the Greek Army there is enclosed a <pb
                        facs="0569" n="455" xml:id="pg_455"/> copy of despatch No. 249 of June 1,
                    1922, from the United States High Commissioner at Constantinople. You are
                    instructed to take this matter up with the Foreign Office making urgent
                    representations that appropriate instructions be sent by the Greek Minister of
                    War to the local Greek military commanders in Asia Minor that they cease
                    impressing American citizens of Ottoman or Greek origin into the Greek
                        Army.<note n="33" xml:id="d377fn33">With this instruction the correspondence
                        in regard to the impressment of American naturalized citizens into the Greek
                        Army was temporarily discontinued.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
